{{M1 year in topic}}
[[File:Otto II, Holy Roman Emperor.jpg|{{Largethumb}}|right|[[Otto II, Holy Roman Emperor|Otto II]] ('''the Red''') (955–983)]]
Year '''982''' ('''[[Roman numerals|CMLXXXII]]''') was a [[common year starting on Sunday]] (link will display the full calendar) of the [[Julian calendar]].

== Events ==
&lt;onlyinclude&gt;

=== By place ===
==== Europe ====
* Summer &amp;ndash; Emperor [[Otto II, Holy Roman Emperor|Otto II]] ('''the Red''') assembles an imperial expeditionary force at [[Taranto]] and proceeds along the gulf coast towards [[Calabria]]. In the meantime, [[Abu'l-Qasim Ali ibn al-Hasan al-Kalbi|Abu'l-Qasim]] ([[Kalbids|Kalbid]] emir of the [[Emirate of Sicily]]), declares a [[Religious war|Holy War]] (''[[jihad]]'') against the Germans, but retreats his forces when he notice the unexpected strength of Otto's troops (not far from [[Rossano]]).
* [[July 13]] (or [[July 14|14]]) &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Stilo]]: Abu'l-Qasim is cornered by the imperial German forces led by Otto II at [[Capo Colonna|Cape Colonna]] (south of [[Crotone]]). After a violent clash, the German heavy cavalry destroys the Muslim centre, killing al-Qasim in the initial fighting. The [[Saracens]] hold together, draws Otto into a trap, encircling and defeating his forces (killing around 4,000 men).&lt;ref&gt;Reuter, Timothy (1999). ''The New Cambridge Medieval History, Volume III'', p. 255. {{ISBN|978-0-521-36447-8}}.&lt;/ref&gt;
* King [[Harald Bluetooth]] invades [[Norway]], pillaging south-west Norway all the way to [[Stad (peninsula)|Stad]], where he encounters [[Haakon Sigurdsson]] (the ''[[de facto]]'' ruler of Norway) and his army. He flees back to [[Denmark]], ending the invasion.

==== Arabian Empire ====
* [['Adud al-Dawla]], emir (''[[king of kings]]'') of the [[Buyid dynasty|Buyid Dynasty]], concludes a 10-year [[peace treaty]] with the [[Byzantine Empire]]. He establishes what will soon become the most important [[Bimarestan|hospital]] of [[Baghdad]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|title=Islamic Culture and the Medical Arts_Hospitals|url=https://www.nlm.nih.gov/exhibition/islamic_medical/islamic_12.html|accessdate=8 November 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;

==== China ====
* [[October 13]] &amp;ndash; Emperor [[Emperor Jingzong of Liao|Jing Zong]] dies (during a [[hunting]] trip) after a 13-year reign. He is succeeded by his 12-year-old son, [[Emperor Shengzong of Liao|Sheng Zong]], as ruler of the [[Khitan people|Khitan]]-led [[Liao dynasty|Liao Dynasty]]. His mother, Empress Dowager [[Empress Xiao Yanyan|Xiao Yanyan]] becomes the [[regent]].

=== By topic ===
==== Exploration ====
* [[Erik the Red]] establishes the first [[Vikings|Viking]] colonies in [[Greenland]] (see [[981]]).

==== Religion ====
* [[Adalbert of Prague|Adalbert]] becomes bishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Prague|Prague]] after the death of [[Dětmar]] (or '''Dietmar''').
&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;

== Births ==
* [[Atiśa]], Bengali [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] religious leader (d. [[1054]])
* [[Dirk III, Count of Holland|Dirk III]] (or '''Theodoric'''), count of [[County of Holland|Holland]] (d. [[1039]])
* [[Judith of Brittany]], duchess of [[Duchy of Normandy|Normandy]] (d. [[1017]])

== Deaths ==
* [[January 2]] &amp;ndash; [[Dětmar]] (or '''Dietmar'''), bishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Prague|Prague]]
* [[July 13]] (or [[July 14|14]]) &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Stilo]]:
** [[Abu'l-Qasim Ali ibn al-Hasan al-Kalbi|Abu'l-Qasim]], Kalbid [[emir]] of [[Emirate of Sicily|Sicily]]
** [[Gunther, Margrave of Merseburg|Gunther]], margrave of [[March of Merseburg|Merseburg]]
** [[Henry I (bishop of Augsburg)|Henry I]], bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Augsburg|Augsburg]]
** [[Landulf IV of Benevento|Landulf IV]], Lombard prince
** [[Pandulf II of Salerno|Pandulf II]], Lombard prince 
* [[October 13]] &amp;ndash; [[Emperor Jingzong of Liao|Jing Zong]], emperor of the [[Liao dynasty|Liao Dynasty]] (b. [[948]])
* [[November 26]] &amp;ndash; [[Matilda of France|Matilda]], queen of [[Burgundy]] (or [[981]])
* [[Abu'l Haret Muhammad]], Farighunid ruler (approximate date)
* [[Abu'l-Husain Utbi]], Samanid [[vizier]]
* [[Al-Hasan ibn Ubayd Allah ibn Tughj]], Ikhshidid prince and [[regent]]
* [[Eadwine of Sussex|Eadwine]], ealdorman of [[Kingdom of Sussex|Sussex]] (approximate date)
* [[Gao Huaide]], Chinese general (b. [[926]])
* [[Indra IV]], Rashtrakuta ruler ([[India]])
* [[Jordan (Bishop of Poland)|Jordan]], bishop of [[Greater Poland|Poland]] (or [[984]])
* [[Otto I, Duke of Swabia and Bavaria|Otto I]], duke of [[Duchy of Swabia|Swabia]] and [[Duchy of Bavaria|Bavaria]] (b. [[954]])
* [[Senorina]], Galician [[abbess]] and saint
* [[Shabbethai Donnolo]], Jewish physician (b. [[913]])
* [[Wang Pu (Song dynasty)|Wang Pu]], Chinese [[Grand chancellor (China)|chancellor]] (b. [[922]])

